Comment[B wins by 2.5 zi \(5 points\).

Overview: In this game, the variations at upper left, upper right, and lower left three corners were interesting and spectacular.  A remarkable fact was that even W seemed to lose at the upper left, from a global point of view, W wasn't exactly lagging.  In other words, Fan and Shi had the ability to control the global situation over local details.  They once again lived up
with the title of "Great National Hands."]
